---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Scaling Thoughts" description="About Abhinav - Software Engineer at Amazon">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-4">
        About
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <!-- Profile section -->
      <div class="not-prose flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 items-start mb-8">
        <img
          src="/profile.jpg"
          alt="Abhinav"
          class="w-32 h-32 rounded-full object-cover"
        />
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Abhinav</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            Software Engineer at Amazon<br />
            Seattle, WA
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-4 mt-3">
            <a href="https://github.com/abhinavsv3" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gray-500 hover:text-accent dark:hover:text-accent-dark">GitHub</a>
            <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/abhinavsv3" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gray-500 hover:text-accent dark:hover:text-accent-dark">LinkedIn</a>
            <a href="https://twitter.com/abhinavsv3" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gray-500 hover:text-accent dark:hover:text-accent-dark">Twitter</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        Hi, I'm Abhinav.
      </p>

      <p>
        I'm a Software Engineer at <strong>Amazon</strong>, currently working on ML infrastructure
        for computational biology in the Special Projects group.
      </p>

      <p>
        I like building things from scratch—taking ambiguous problems and shipping real solutions.
        My recent work includes prompt optimization across foundation models, published at the
        Amazon Machine Learning Conference (2025).
      </p>

      <h2>Background</h2>
      <p>
        I did my Master's at the <strong>University of Florida</strong>, focusing on graph and matrix
        algorithms for visualizing high-dimensional data. Before that, I studied at
        <strong>SASTRA University</strong> in India.
      </p>

      <h2>This Blog</h2>
      <p>
        Scaling Thoughts is where I think out loud about engineering, ML, and whatever I'm learning.
        Writing helps clarify thinking—and hopefully helps others along the way.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
